There are several algorithms to estimate the effective reproduction number from the data: a simplified one is given in [20], where also an extensive bibliography on the subject can be found. The simplest yet effective estimate that very directly interprets the meaning of the function (see, for instance, [21]) is given by8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} {\mathcal {R}}_t \,=\, \frac{I(t+{\mathbf {g}})}{I(t)}\,. \end{aligned}$$\end{document}Rt=I(t+g)I(t).As far as the SIR model is concerned, from Eq. 4b  one has9\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} {\mathcal {R}}_{t} \,=\, \frac{{\mathbf {r}}}{I(t)}\, \frac{I(t+{\mathbf {g}}+1)-I(t+{\mathbf {g}}-1)}{2} \,+\, \frac{I(t+{\mathbf {g}}-{\mathbf {r}})}{I(t)}\,. \end{aligned}$$\end{document}Rt=rI(t)I(t+g+1)-I(t+g-1)2+I(t+g-r)I(t).So, the derivative is implemented by the symmetric difference quotient, to have the cancellation of the first-order error in the numerical discretization.

